<div class='title'>
  <h3>Settings</h3>
  <button id='popup-close' class='close'>Close</button>
</div>
<hr />
<div class='content'>

  <section>
    <p>
      Currently, the settings can't actually be changed, because that logic needs building. But it's next on the list, so for the moment, just imagine how useful it will be when you can change them!
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h4>Key Map</h4>
    <p>The editor keymapping can be changed with the <em>keymap</em> query argument. Currently the supported bindings are the CodeMirror defaults and Vim bindings</p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#">Default Keymap</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">Vim Keymap</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h4>Transparent Background</h4>
    <p>This will make the entire background of the editor transparent, so it's possible to sit the editor ontop of the visuals</p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#">Enable Transparency</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">Disable Transparency</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h4>Performance Mode</h4>
    <p>Enabling performance mode will hide the header bar so that there can be more canvas visible</p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#">Enable Performance Mode</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">Disable Performance Mode</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h4>Line Numbers</h4>
    <p>Line numbers can be added to the editor with the <em>linenumbers</em> query argument.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#">Enable Line Numbers</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">Disable Line Numbers</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</div>
